This article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate. The letter discusses the continuation of a national emergency with respect to foreign terrorists who threaten to disrupt the Middle East peace process. The President explains that the crisis with these terrorists has not been resolved and that they continue to engage in activities that threaten the peace process and are hostile to US interests in the region. The President determines that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain economic sanctions against these terrorists in response to the threat they pose.